Prevent concurrent task from undoing filter

It could happen that after new entry is fetched:
1. add_readability is called first and grabs reference to entry
2. filter is called, matches entry and marks it as archived
3. add_readability receives data from remote URL and calls entry.save()

But entry changed between step 1 and 3, so step 3 effectively overwrites
any change done in step 2.

This should no longer happen.

Don't call dateutil parser on date received from Celery

Since Kombu 5.3.0 (part of Celery 5.3.0), Celery will automatically
support datetime objects when using json serializer. In other words - we
return object with datetime field, and then when we retrieve Celery
result, we get datetime field automatically. Trying to call dateutil
parser now will result in exception, which completely breaks content
autodetection.

Set minimum Python version to 3.10, update dependencies

since version 3.9. However, now that Python 3.12 has been released, it's
good idea to bump minimum Python version anyway.
